<text>Stop

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

The stop command causes the simulation to stop. If there is a recorder, the simulation stops at the next recording step (there therefore can be a brief delay). Otherwise, it stops immediately.

Syntax:

stop
stop immediately

The stop command causes exactly the same effect as clicking the &quot;stop&quot; button of the simulator&apos;s control panel. To force the simulation to stop immediately when there is a recorder, add the immediately keyword to the command.

Note that this command does not stop the execution of the current scripts. To terminate the execution of the scripts from inside the scripts, use the return command.

